What warnings does critTer generate on your Part 3 code, and what are
your disagreements with them? Copy the critTer warnings here, and
express your disagreement after each warning. If there are no
warnings, then write "None."

(1) nodeFT.c: line 58: low priority:
   "A function should consist of fewer than 140 lines;
    this function consists of 151 lines; consider refactoring"
Exempt per assignment instructions (too long function).

(2) nodeFT.c: line 493: low priority:
   "A file should contain no more than 15 functions;
    this file contains 16 functions"
Exempt per assignment instructions (too many functions).

(3) nodeFT.c: line 474: low priority:
   "This area is deeply nested at level 4, consider refactoring"
Exempt per assignment instructions (too deeply nested).

(4) ft.c: line 126: low priority:
   "A loop should consist of fewer than 35 lines;
    this loop consists of 40 lines; consider refactoring"
Exempt per assignment instructions (too long loop).

(5) nodeFT.h: line 18: high priority:
   "A comment should appear above each global variable."
We disagree. There is a comment immediately above the NodeType
typedef on line 17: "Enumeration to differentiate between directory
and file nodes." critTer misidentifies this typedef as a global
variable requiring a separate comment.

(6) nodeFT.c: line 235: medium priority:
   "Do you want to validate 'pvNewContents' through an assert?"
We disagree. pvNewContents can legitimately be NULL when clearing
a file's contents or creating an empty file. Adding an assert would
break valid use cases.

(7) ft.c: line 89: medium priority:
   "Do you want to validate 'pvContents' through an assert?"
We disagree. pvContents can legitimately be NULL for empty files
or directories. The function handles NULL pvContents correctly.

(8) ft.c: line 270: medium priority:
   "Do you want to validate 'pvContents' through an assert?"
We disagree. Same reasoning as (7). FT_insertFile allows NULL
pvContents for files with no initial content.

(9) ft.c: line 363: medium priority:
   "Do you want to validate 'pvNewContents' through an assert?"
We disagree. Same reasoning as (6). FT_replaceFileContents allows
NULL pvNewContents to clear a file's contents.



